article_title: Analysis: Fed on Track for Rate Rise
article_text:
The strong May employment report likely keeps the Federal Reserve on track to start raising short-term interest rates later this year, but officials are unlikely to move at their policy meeting this month because they want to see more evidence of a solid economic expansion.

Fed officials signaled before the job report Friday that they had moved into a wait-and-see stance ahead of the June 16-17 meeting, their confidence shaken by an...
